title: Train services to Mumbai affected due to equipment snag
text:
MUMBAI: A snag in the overhead equipment on the CR main line between Thane and Mulund UP fast line has affected train services to Mumbai since 6.31pm.
Two trains were held up on section while others were being diverted on the slow line between Diva and Mulund. The late evening peak hour services could be affected as trains are bound to reach CST late.
"There was a snag reported few minutes back and our team is on the spot attending to the problem. Fast trains towards CST have been diverted on slow track between Diva and Mulund," informed a railway official. http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/followceleb.cms?alias=UP fast line has affected train services,Train services to Mumbai,reach CST late,CR main line between Thane and Mulund,affected due to equipment snag Stay updated on the go with Times of India News App. Click here to download it for your device.
